male: “MALAYA \ (Pahang) \ Genling-0002. \ 16. 
<collectionCode id="ED337CD5C001FFC76B762F69DE1BFA85" box="[1056,1087,1359,1380]" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">IV</collectionCode>
[?]. 74 \ 
<collectorName id="26D781C6C001FFC76BDA2F69DEC0FA85" box="[1164,1252,1359,1380]" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">P. Roche</collectorName>
” [handwritten]; “7569.” [handwritten]; “Ex-coll. \ 
<collectorName id="26D781C6C001FFC76B332F4ADEC8FA60" box="[1125,1260,1388,1409]" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">P.J.L. Roche</collectorName>
” [printed] (Nationaal Natuurhistorische Museum, Leiden, 
<collectingCountry id="F335A480C001FFC76BF02FAFDF1AFA7F" box="[1190,1342,1417,1438]" name="Netherlands" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">the Netherlands</collectingCountry>
). The specimen is micropinned and in good condition, apart from segment I of the left antenna being glued to a triangular card and pinned under the specimen, the apex of the femur and tibia and tarsus of the right mid leg and both hind legs are missing. The pygophore is removed from the body and glued on a card separately, the phallus is preserved in glycerol in a plastic microvial, pinned with the specimen.
